# Patterns that force an "ask before write" prompt — applies to Write/Edit
# tools and to inferred Bash write targets (redirects, tee, sed -i, mv/cp).
# Same pattern shapes as ask-before-read, plus !pattern negation: a path
# matched by a !-prefixed pattern is never gated, even if a positive pattern
# also matches.

.env
.env.*
id_rsa
id_ed25519
id_ecdsa
id_dsa
*.pem
*.key
~/.ssh/
~/.aws/credentials
~/.aws/config
~/.netrc
~/.git-credentials
~/.config/gh/hosts.yml
~/.config/gh/config.yml
~/.bash_history
~/.zsh_history
~/.gitconfig
CLAUDE.md
# Blanket-gate any .claude/ directory — home or project-local. Catches
# hooks/, agents/, commands/, plugins/, skills/, config/, settings.json,
# .credentials.json, and any future subdirs Claude Code adds. Carve out
# only ~/.claude/plans/ (Claude writes plan files there in plan mode).
# Project plans/ is NOT carved out — a malicious repo could otherwise drop
# behavior-modifying files there.
.claude/
!~/.claude/plans/
